1. The p-value to be 0.0 (with 1E-3 tolerance)
2. The chi-square test statistic to be 114875.90421929007 (with 1E-9 tolerance)

Let me identify the issue. The problem likely lies in the calculation of the chi-square test where large values could cause numerical problems. Looking at the `chiSquare` method in `ChiSquareTestImpl.java`, I can see the calculation:

```java
for (int i = 0; i < observed.length; i++) {
    dev = ((double) observed[i] - expected[i]);
    sumSq += dev * dev / expected[i];
}
```

